They will not help sag from inrush to the motor and their spike suppression
will not deal with back emf from a motor of any size especially if driven by a
poorly designed switch mode power supply.

The Warehouse were selling black 4 way plugboards with surge suppression for
$4.99. Perhaps they still do.

It would probably be worth trying running a heater on the same power point as
the walker, but keep it down to 1200W to avoid overloading the circuit. That
should damp the worst inductive excursions.

Power factor correction may help on the walker. Depends on how it's built.

Walking outside is much more attractive these days.
